sume` | (Not a skill) |\n| Session >30 tool calls | 💡 `/reflect` | (Not a skill) |\n| Build failure | 🔧 `/build-fix` | (Not in .claude/skills) |\n| Pre-release | 🏷️ `/release` | release/SKILL.md |\n\n---\n\n### Deployed Skills Analysis — 19 Total\n\n**WITH \"Next Step\" sections (5 skills):**\n- ✓ **spec** — \"After the spec file is written, run `/spec-validate NNN` to score it before execution, or jump straight to `/spec-work NNN` to start implementation.\"\n- ✓ **spec-work** — \"After implementation: `/spec-review NNN` to validate, then `/commit`, `/pr`, or `/spec-board` depending on the review outcome.\"\n- ✓ **spec-board** — \"To work on a spec, run `/spec-work NNN`. To validate a draft spec before starting, run `/spec-validate NNN`.\"\n- ✓ **reflect** — \"After saving learnings, run `/apply-learnings` to distribute new entries from LEARNINGS.md... Then run `/commit` to checkpoint all changes, or `/pause` to end the session cleanly.\"\n- ✓ **session-optimize** — \"Review findings and pick top items to address. For each fix: open a spec (`/spec`) or apply directly if it's a single-line change.\"\n\n**WITHOUT \"Next Step\" sections (14 skills — CRITICAL GAPS):**\n- ✗ **agent-browser** — no hint\n- ✗ **apply-learnings** — no hint\n- ✗ **bash-defensive-patterns** — no hint\n- ✗ **context-load** — no hint\n- ✗ **context-refresh** — no hint\n- ✗ **explore** — no hint (should suggest next steps for exploration outcomes)\n- ✗ **gh-cli** — no hint\n- ✗ **orchestrate** — no hint\n- ✗ **release** — **CRITICAL** — no hint after successful release\n- ✗ **spec-review** — **CRITICAL** — no hint about finishing gates or committing\n- ✗ **spec-run** — no hint about review/commit flow\n- ✗ **spec-run-all** — no hint about parallel execution completion\n- ✗ **spec-validate** — **CRITICAL** — verdict shows \"Run `/spec-work NNN`\" but no formal \"Next Step\" section\n- ✗ **commit** — **CRITICAL** — only suggests `/reflect` but missing `/pr` or `/release` guidance\n\n---\n\n### Template Skills Coverage (35 templates total)\n\n**WITH \"Next Step\" sections (21 templates):**\n- ✓ analyze, build-fix, challenge, ci, debug, discover, doctor, lint, pause, reflect, research, resume, review, scan, spec, spec-board, spec-work, techdebt, test, test-setup, update\n\n**WITHOUT \"Next Step\" sections (14 templates):**\n- ✗ apply-learnings, commit, context-load, context-refresh, explore, orchestrate, pr, release, spec-review, spec-run, spec-run-all, spec-validate, spec-work-all, token-optimizer\n\n**Key observations:**\n- Template library is MORE complete than deployment (21/35 = 60% vs 5/19 = 26%)\n- Critical workflow skills are underrepresented in deployments (spec-validate, spec-review, commit, pr, release deployed but incomplete)\n\n---\n\n### Onboarding & Discovery Guidance\n\n**STRENGTHS:**\n\n1. **README.md** — Excellent overview with 35 skills listed, including descriptions and model assignments\n2. **WORKFLOW-GUIDE.md** — Comprehensive German-language workflow guide with:\n   - Quick Start section\n   - Onboarding commands table\n   - Development cycle with numbered steps (1-8)\n   - Hotfix flow\n   - Session management\n3. **specs/README.md** — Clear spec lifecycle and naming conventions\n4. **CLAUDE.md template** — Documents model routing, permission modes, automation patterns\n\n**WEAKNESSES:**\n\n1. **No \"getting started\" checklist** — New users don't know to run `/doctor` first, `/analyze` second\n2. **Skills not cross-referenced** — Workflow hints are only in the workflow.md table; skills themselves don't reference the routing table\n3. **No skill discovery help** — Users must read individual SKILL.md files to find next steps; there's no `suggest-next-skill` mechanism\n4. **Session handoff incomplete** — `/pause` and `/resume` exist but post-commit/post-release flows don't mention them\n5. **No \"failed skill\" recovery** — When a skill fails or blocks, no guidance on what to do next\n\n---\n\n### Critical Missing Hints (by workflow position)\n\nFrom the routing table, these should trigger hints but don't:\n\n1. **After `/spec-validate`** (template has, deployed doesn't) — Should suggest: \"Grade A/B: Run `/spec-work NNN`. Grade C: Fix and re-run. Grade F: Major revision needed.\"\n\n2. **After `/commit`** (incomplete in both) — Should suggest: \"Run `/pr` to create pull request, or `/release` if this is the main branch.\"\n\n3. **After `/release`** (completely missing) — Should suggest: \"Released vX.Y.Z. Push tags: `git push && git push --tags`. Next: monitor CI/CD or `/pr` for dependent changes.\"\n\n4. **After `/spec-review` APPROVED** (completely missing) — Should suggest: \"Spec approved. Choose finishing gate: merge to main, push branch, or keep branch local. Then run `/commit` or `/pr`.\"\n\n5. **After `/pr` creation** (template missing) — Should suggest: \"PR drafted. Review & merge via GitHub, or run `/ci` to check status.\"\n\n6. **After `/test` success** (not a deployed skill, but templates have it) — Should suggest: \"Tests pass. Run `/review` to audit changes, then `/commit`.\"\n\n---\n\n### Recommendations for Guided Experience\n\n**Priority 1 — Critical Workflow Completeness:**\n\n1. Add \"## Next Step\" section to `/spec-validate` SKILL.md:\n   ```\n   Based on grade: A/B → \"Run `/spec-work NNN`\"\n   C → \"Fix items scoring <7, re-run `/spec-validate NNN`\"\n   F → \"Major revisions needed. Use AskUserQuestion with options to revise or abandon.\"\n   ```\n\n2. Add \"## Next Step\" to `/spec-review` SKILL.md:\n   ```\n   APPROVED → \"Choose finishing gate: merge, push branch, or keep. Then run `/commit` to document changes, or `/pr` to create pull request.\"\n   CHANGES REQUESTED → \"Address feedback in spec, re-run `/spec-work NNN`\"\n   REJECTED → \"Fix critical issues before re-reviewing.\"\n   ```\n\n3. Add \"## Next Step\" to `/commit` SKILL.md:\n   ```\n   After successful commit, suggest: \"Run `/reflect` to capture learnings, then `/pr` to create pull request (if feature branch) or `/release` if main branch.\"\n   ```\n\n4. Add \"## Next Step\" to `/release` SKILL.md:\n   ```\n   After tagging: \"Tagged vX.Y.Z. Run: git push && git push --tags. Monitor CI/CD, or `/pr` if dependent changes needed.\"\n   ```\n\n**Priority 2 — Discovery & Onboarding:**\n\n1. Create `.claude/ONBOARDING.md` with:\n   - First-time checklist: `/doctor` → `/analyze` → `/spec-board`\n   - Workflow diagram showing skill transitions\n   - Decision tree for \"what skill to use next\"\n\n2. Add a \"skill discovery\" mechanism — e.g., a comment in commit output suggesting relevant next skills based on context\n\n3. Reference `.claude/rules/workflow.md` in every skill's \"Next Step\" section to make the routing table visible\n\n**Priority 3 — User Experience Enhancements:**\n\n1. Add post-skill prompts like: `AskUserQuestion: \"What's next?\" with auto-suggestions from workflow routing table based on current skill`\n\n2. Create a skill-chaining system where successful skill completion automatically offers the next workflow step\n\n3. Add workflow progress visualization in `/spec-board` that shows: draft → validate → work → review → commit → pr/release\n\n---\n\n### Conclusion\n\nThe project has an **excellent workflow design** defined in `.claude/rules/workflow.md`, but the **actual skill implementations are inconsistent**. Only 26% of deployed skills (5/19) have \"Next Step\" guidance, while 60% of template skills do. This creates a **friction point for users**: they complete a task but don't know what to do next without consulting documentation.\n\n**Impact:** New users will experience a broken guided experience. Power users will rely on `.claude/rules/workflow.md` and their memory. The system is documented but not self-guiding.\n\n**Fix effort:** Moderate — adding \"## Next Step\" sections to 14 deployed skills + creating onboarding docs would dramatically improve the experience."}
