ctions Taken:\n1. Ran bash .claude/scripts/commit-prep.sh → NO_STAGED_CHANGES\n2. Checked git status - many unstaged changes\n3. Staged only skill files: git add .claude/skills/*/SKILL.md templates/skills/*/SKILL.md\n4. Created commit: \"feat(skills): add workflow hints and model routing to all skills\"\n5. 34 files changed, 227 insertions(+), 39 deletions(-)\n6. Commit hash: be995e4\n\n## /release Skill Invoked\nUser typed \"/release\". Skill expanded to full release process.\n\n### Phase 1: Pre-flight\n- git status showed 36 uncommitted files (from prior sessions)\n- No staged changes (git diff --cached was empty)\n- Modified files: hooks, scripts, README, WORKFLOW-GUIDE, lib files, settings, etc.\n\n### User decision: \"Erst alles committen (Empfohlen)\"\nStaged and committed 37 files:\n- Hooks: cli-health, context-loader, context-monitor, file-index, pre-compact-state, protect-and-breaker, spec-stop-guard, tdd-checker, transcript-ingest, subagent-start (new)\n- Scripts: release.sh\n- Settings: .claude/settings.json, templates/claude/settings.json\n- Docs: README, WORKFLOW-GUIDE, CLAUDE.md\n- Lib: global-settings.sh, migrate.sh, setup.sh\n- Tests: smoke.sh, claude-runtime.sh (new)\n- Commit: \"chore: stage accumulated hook, settings, and test improvements\"\n- Commit hash: 94f8c2c, 37 files changed, 1263 insertions(+), 295 deletions(-)\n\n### npm run verify:release\n- First run (in sandbox): EXIT CODE 1 due to mktemp failing (sandbox restriction on /var/folders/...)\n- Test \"Session extract active duration\" failed\n- All other tests passed\n\n### Sandbox Question from User:\n\"woher kommt der Sandbox-Bypass? Von unserem Setup? Können wir das lockern\"\n\nResponse: Sandbox comes from Claude Code itself, not our setup. Configured via filesystem permissions that block /var/folders. Can be loosened via /sandbox command or by fixing test to use $TMPDIR.\n\n### verify:release with dangerouslyDisableSandbox:\n- EXIT_CODE=0\n- All tests passed: 21 passed, 0 failed, 2 skipped\n- claude-runtime tests all PASS\n\n### Phase 2: Inventory Audit\nFilesystem counts:\n- Commands: 20\n- Agents: 12 (including README.md = 11 actual)\n- Hooks (settings.json): 22 (but templates/hooks: 25)\n- Skills: 19 (including skill-creator-workspace = 18 actual)\n- Rules: 7\n\ndocs-audit.sh found 3 discrepancies:\n- README.md shows \"11 hooks\" but filesystem has 25\n- WORKFLOW-GUIDE.md also shows 11 hooks\n- Hook list in README missing: circuit-breaker, cli-health, context-freshness, context-monitor, context-reinforcement, file-index, mcp-health, permission-denied-log, post-compact-restore, pre-compact-state, protect-files, spec-stop-guard, subagent-start, subagent-stop, tdd-checker, tool-redirect\n\n### User's Target Version: v2.0.8\nUser sent \"v2.0.8\" as a message indicating the target version.\n\n## Status at Summary Request\nCurrently in Phase 3 (Documentation Sync) of the release process. Need to update hook counts and hook list in README.md and WORKFLOW-GUIDE.md from 11 → 25, adding the missing 14 hooks to both files.\n\nThe template hooks list (25 hooks):\ncircuit-breaker, cli-health, config-change-audit, context-freshness, context-loader, context-monitor, context-reinforcement, file-index, mcp-health, memory-recall, notify, permission-denied-log, post-compact-restore, post-edit-lint, post-tool-failure-log, pre-compact-state, protect-files, spec-stop-guard, subagent-start, subagent-stop, task-completed-gate, tdd-checker, tool-redirect, transcript-ingest, update-check\n\nREADME.md line 32 currently reads:\n`| **Hooks** | 11 hooks — context-loader, protect-and-breaker, post-edit-lint, update-check, memory-recall, notify, config-change-audit, task-completed-gate, post-tool-failure-log, transcript-ingest, pre-compact |`\n\nNeeds to be updated to 25 hooks with full list.\n</analysis>\n\n<summary>\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user had three sequential requests:\n   1. **Check workflow guidance**: Verify if the skill system properly guides users with hints about when to use each skill\n   2. **Add hints to ALL skills**: After audit showed only 26% had hints, user chose to add `## Next Step` sections to all skills (both deployed and templates)\n   3. **Find similar optimizations**: Discover other consistency gaps in the skill system (like missing hints), leading to: template/deployed parity sync and adding `model:` frontmatter to all deployed skills\n   4. **Commit** the skill improvements via `/commit`\n   5. **Release v2.0.8** via `/release` — currently in progress at Phase 3 (docs sync)\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - **Skill system**: `SKILL.md` files in `.claude/skills/` (deployed) and `templates/skills/` (installed into user projects)\n   - **Next Step hints**: `## Next Step` sections at end of skills that guide users to the next workflow action\n   - **Model routing**: `model:` frontmatter field in SKILL.md (haiku/sonnet/opus) controlling which Claude model executes the skill\n   - **Workflow routing table**: `.claude/rules/workflow.md` defines \"After X → suggest Y\" but skills weren't implementing it\n   - **YAML frontmatter**: `name:`, `description:`, `model:`, `allowed-tools:`, `mode:` fields in SKILL.md\n   - **Release process**: verify:release → inventory audit → docs sync → version bump → slack → commit + tag\n   - **Claude Code Sandbox**: Filesystem restrictions blocking `/var/folders/...` — affects `mktemp` in tests; bypassed with `dangerouslyDisableSandbox: true`\n   - **docs-audit.sh**: Script that compares filesystem counts vs README/WORKFLOW-GUIDE stated counts\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   **Deployed Skills with added `## Next Step`:**\n   - `.claude/skills/spec-validate/SKILL.md`: Added grade-dependent hints + `model: haiku`\n   - `.claude/skills/spec-review/SKILL.md`: Added verdict-dependent hints + `model: sonnet`\n   - `.claude/skills/release/SKILL.md`: Added push tags hint + `model: sonnet`\n   - `.claude/skills/spec-run/SKILL.md`: Added /spec-board hint + `model: sonnet`\n   - `.claude/skills/spec-run-all/SKILL.md`: Added /spec-board hint + `model: sonnet`\n   - `.claude/skills/context-refresh/SKILL.md`: Added continue working hint + `model: haiku`\n   - `.claude/skills/context-load/SKILL.md`: Added continue working hint + `model: haiku`\n   - `.claude/skills/explore/SKILL.md`: Added /spec hint + `model: haiku`\n   - `.claude/skills/apply-learnings/SKILL.md`: Added /commit hint + `model: sonnet`\n   - `.claude/skills/orchestrate/SKILL.md`: Added continue/commit hint + `model: sonnet`\n   - `.claude/skills/spec-board/SKILL.md`: Added `model: haiku`\n   - `.claude/skills/spec-work/SKILL.md`: Added `model: sonnet`\n   - `.claude/skills/spec/SKILL.md`: Added `model: opus`\n   - `.claude/skills/gh-cli/SKILL.md`: Added `model: haiku`\n   - `.claude/skills/bash-defensive-patterns/SKILL.md`: Added `model: haiku`\n   - `.claude/skills/agent-browser/SKILL.md`: Added `model: haiku`\n\n   **Templates with added `## Next Step`:**\n   - `templates/skills/spec-validate/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/spec-review/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/release/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/spec-run/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/spec-run-all/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/context-refresh/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/context-load/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/explore/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/apply-learnings/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/orchestrate/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/token-optimizer/SKILL.md`\n   - `templates/skills/commit/SKILL.md`: Changed Post-Commit to `## Next Step` with branch-aware hints (Feature→/pr, Main→/release)\n   - `templates/skills/pr/SKILL.md`: Changed Post-PR to `## Next Step` with /ci hint\n   - `templates/skills/spec-work-all/SKILL.md`\n\n   **Template sync (spec):**\n   - `templates/skills/spec/SKILL.md`: Added Code-Flow-Analyse block, Step Dedup Check, Step dedup validation after drafting — bringing template up to deployed skill's quality level\n\n   **Pre-release commits:**\n   - Commit `be995e4`: \"feat(skills): add workflow hints and model routing to all skills\" — 34 files, 227 insertions\n   - Commit `94f8c2c`: \"chore: stage accumulated hook, settings, and test improvements\" — 37 files, 1263 insertions, new files: `subagent-start.sh` (deployed + template), `tests/claude-runtime.sh`\n\n   **README.md line 32 (needs update):**\n   ```\n   | **Hooks** | 11 hooks — context-loader, protect-and-breaker, post-edit-lint, update-check, memory-recall, notify, config-change-audit, task-completed-gate, post-tool-failure-log, transcript-ingest, pre-compact |\n   ```\n   Needs to reflect 25 hooks.\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **`git add` with newlines**: First attempt used line-continuation in git add which failed with \"Pfadspezifikation ' ' stimmt mit keinen Dateien überein\". Fixed by putting all paths on a single line.\n   - **`! bash` command**: The `!` prefix for shell commands doesn't work inside the Bash tool. Fixed by calling `bash .claude/scripts/commit-prep.sh` directly.\n   - **`git add` for spec-board and spec-work**: Edit tool rejected because files hadn't been read first. Fixed by reading the first 5 lines of each file, then editing.\n   - **mktemp sandbox failure**: `tests/smoke.sh` \"Session extract active duration\" test calls `mktemp` on `/var/folders/...` which is outside Claude Code's sandbox. In-sandbox run returns EXIT_CODE=1. Fixed by running with `dangerouslyDisableSandbox: true` → EXIT_CODE=0, all tests pass.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - **Skill guidance gap**: 74% of deployed skills had no workflow hints. Solved by systematically adding `## Next Step` to all 13 missing deployed skills and 14 missing template skills.\n   - **Model routing missing**: 15/18 deployed skills had no `model:` field, causing them to inherit parent session model (potentially expensive Opus calls). Solved by classifying each skill as haiku (read-only/reference), sonnet (implementation), or opus (architecture) and adding explicit field.\n   - **Temp