his architectural principle if any hooks depend on skills that call scripts.\n\n**Recommendation:** Any implementation of `disableSkillShellExecution` should:\n1. Provide explicit warning when toggling for projects using these 6 skills\n2. Document fallback workflows (e.g., manual `doctor.sh` invocation)\n3. Consider a whitelist/blacklist mechanism rather than blanket disablement, given the critical nature of doctor and review automation"}
